  stimulus_text = 'While on his journey through the countryside, the narrator is struck by the beauty of his surroundings, particularly the river. He describes the river as a “serene and winding ribbon of water” that flows through the landscape, “a constant companion” to his travels. The narrator is also drawn to the birds that he sees, describing their songs as “sweet melodies that fill the air.” This description of the natural world conveys a sense of peace and tranquility, a feeling of being at one with nature. What is the most likely reason why the author uses the phrase “serene and winding ribbon of water” to describe the river?',
